# Project Overview — get-job-assistent

A NestJS backend that scrapes LinkedIn job listings via Apify, normalizes and stores them in PostgreSQL, and scores them against candidate profiles.

## Tech Stack

- **Runtime:** Node 22, TypeScript (ES2023, `nodenext` modules)
- **Framework:** NestJS 11 (`@nestjs/common`, `core`, `platform-express`)
- **Database:** PostgreSQL 16 via TypeORM (`synchronize: false`, migrations only)
- **Queue:** BullMQ + Redis 7 (`@nestjs/bullmq`)
- **External API:** Apify Client (LinkedIn Jobs Scraper actor)
- **Infra:** Docker Compose (postgres:16-alpine, redis:7-alpine, app)

## Project Structure

```
src/
├── main.ts                  # NestFactory bootstrap, REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS, PORT
├── AppModule.ts             # Root: ConfigModule (global), TypeORM, BullMQ, imports feature modules
├── app.controller.ts        # GET / health
├── app.service.ts
├── config/
│   ├── ormconfig.ts          # Postgres config from POSTGRES_URL env
│   ├── typeormDataSource.ts  # DataSource for CLI migrations
│   └── bullmqConfig.ts      # Redis connection from REDIS_HOST/PORT
└── module/
    ├── apify/                # External API integration module
    │   ├── ApifyModule.ts    # APIFY_CLIENT factory + ApifyLinkedinJobsService
    │   ├── enum/             # ApifyActorsEnum, ContractTypeEnum, ExperienceLevelEnum, WorkTypeEnum, PublishedAtEnum
    │   ├── interface/        # IGetLinkedinJobsParams, IJobDescriptionResponse, etc.
    │   └── service/          # ApifyLinkedinJobsService (run actor → read dataset)
    └── job/                  # Core domain module
        ├── JobModule.ts      # TypeORM entities, BullMQ queue, controller, services, repositories
        ├── controller/       # JobDescriptionController (GET endpoints)
        ├── service/          # JobDescriptionService (ETL pipeline, queue fan-out)
        ├── entity/           # 11 TypeORM entities (see database-conventions rule)
        ├── repository/       # BaseRepository + 11 concrete repos
        ├── queue/            # LinkedinJobsProcessor (BullMQ worker)
        ├── interface/        # Domain interfaces (IJobDescription, ICompany, etc.)
        ├── const/            # LINKEDIN_JOBS_QUEUE, LINKEDIN_JOBS_JOB_NAME
        ├── utils/            # normalizeStringValue
        └── migrations/       # 11 ordered migration files (3 per new table on average)
```

## Module Architecture

- **AppModule** — global config, wires TypeORM + BullMQ roots, imports feature modules
- **ApifyModule** — `APIFY_CLIENT` injection token (factory from ConfigService), exports `ApifyLinkedinJobsService`
- **JobModule** — imports `ApifyModule`, registers all entities via `TypeOrmModule.forFeature`, BullMQ queue `linkedin-jobs`

## Key Patterns

- **Feature-based organization** under `src/module/<feature>/`
- **Constructor injection** everywhere; `@Inject('APIFY_CLIENT')` for factory token; `@InjectQueue` for BullMQ
- **Repository pattern** — abstract `BaseRepository<T>` with `findAll`, `create`, `insertManyIgnoreConflicts`
- **No DTOs / Guards / Pipes / Interceptors / Filters** — minimal HTTP layer, processing triggered via GET endpoints
- **Barrel exports** — each subfolder has `index.ts` re-exporting its members
- **Interfaces** prefixed with `I` (e.g., `IJobDescription`, `ICompany`)
- **No Swagger/OpenAPI** decorators

## Scripts

- `npm run start:dev` — dev with watch
- `npm run migration:generate -- src/module/job/migrations/<name>` — auto-generate
- `npm run migration:run` — apply pending
- `npm run migration:revert` — rollback last
- `npm run lint` — ESLint with `--fix`
- `npm run format` — Prettier
